An appeals court in the Amazon state of Acre yesterday ordered a retrial of
the man convicted of masterminding the murder of Brazilian rainforest
campaigner Chico Mendes, the Estado news agency said, Reuter reports from
Rio de Janeiro
Mr Darli Alves da Silva and his son, Darci were both sentenced to 19 years
in prison in December 1990 for the crime, which shocked conservationists
around the world.
Estado reported that the court turned down Darci's plea for a retrial.
